{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-10-09-how-to-change-marquee-text-color-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To change marquee text color in react js, you can use  in   tag. It will change marquee text color in react js. Today, I am‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To change marquee text color in react js, you can use <code class=\"language-text\">style={{color:\"pink\"}}</code> in  <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;marquee></code> tag. It will change marquee text color in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to change marquee text color in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h2>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 2: Import react component.</h2>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 3: Create a Component.</h2>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">style={{color:\"pink\"}}</code> to change marquee text color in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>marquee width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"60%\"</span> direction<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"right\"</span> height<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"100px\"</span> style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token string\">\"pink\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      This is a sample scrolling text that has scrolls texts to the right<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>marquee<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Change marquee text color example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">'react'</code> and set <code class=\"language-text\">style={{color:\"pink\"}}</code> in  <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;marquee></code> tag to change marquee text color in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">App</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>marquee width<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"60%\"</span> direction<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"right\"</span> height<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"100px\"</span> style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span><span class=\"token string\">\"pink\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      This is a sample scrolling text that has scrolls texts to the right<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>marquee<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">style={{color:\"pink\"}}</code> to change marquee text color in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7aef659981555b133c09ca1efe666309/ec897/marquee-text-color.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-